{
  "_note": "LT6 — DCL pre-clamp pipeline slice (FIRST live test of DclPipelineEnabled). One-switch pipeline: calc-entry probe (0x309A44) caches (caster, actionType, abilityId) per target; the pre-clamp managed callback (0x30A66F) snapshots attacker+target, builds the full formula context (units + equipment via item catalog + ability vars via WotL baseline CSV) and REWRITES the staged debit with DclDamageFormula, same-hit. Force-hit stack from LT5-A4 stays on so every swing connects and every swing produces a [DCL] log line. PASS = each hit's HP drop equals the 'debit' in its [DCL] line AND differs from vanilla 'oldDebit'; [DCL-MISS]/[DCL-ERR] lines = investigate. The formula is a deliberately minimal, predictable slice (attacker PA + weapon power + ability Y), NOT the real damage model.",
